## ===========================================================================
## Home SOC — auditd rules
## Author: Anthony Mackenzi
##
## These keyed watches turn kernel audit events into high-signal detections.
## The key names (identity / priv_esc / netcat) are matched by Wazuh rules in
## detections/wazuh-rules/local_rules.xml via <field name="audit.key">.
##
## Install on an endpoint:
##     sudo cp deploy/audit/homesoc-audit.rules /etc/audit/rules.d/homesoc.rules
##     sudo augenrules --load        # or: sudo service auditd restart
## (scripts/install-agent-linux.sh installs the same content automatically.)
## ===========================================================================

## Identity & credential files  (MITRE T1003, T1098, T1136)
-w /etc/passwd  -p wa -k identity
-w /etc/shadow  -p wa -k identity
-w /etc/group   -p wa -k identity
-w /etc/gshadow -p wa -k identity

## Sudoers / privilege escalation  (MITRE T1548.003)
-w /etc/sudoers   -p wa -k priv_esc
-w /etc/sudoers.d -p wa -k priv_esc

## Reverse-shell / data-transfer tooling  (MITRE T1059, T1095)
-w /usr/bin/nc    -p x -k netcat
-w /bin/nc        -p x -k netcat
-w /usr/bin/ncat  -p x -k netcat
-w /usr/bin/socat -p x -k netcat
